fields.name: Alpaca Wool Blanket - Sand
fields.description:
This super soft blanket is made according to old traditions with hand-spun alpaca wool in a small weavery in Lima, Peru. The geometric pattern is inspired by the textiles of the Inca Empire that has one of the oldest and best preserved traditions of textile arts in the world. Fringes are hand-finished. 

Measurements: 183 cm x 140 cm

Material: 20% alpaca 80% acrylic, leather label

Colour: fuchsia/marsala

We recommend hand wash or dry clean

fields.name: Fine Weave Sisal Basket no.1
fields.description:
Fine weave sisal baskets size: M

These hand woven baskets are made by Basket Weaver Women’s Groups in southeastern Kenya.  Laboriously crafted from thin hand-twisted sisal fibres that are dyed using natural plants. The baskets come in different colours and patterns, making each one unique.

Sisal is an exceptionally strong and sustainable material that grows well in Kenya's harsh climate and no pesticides or chemical fertilizers are used for cultivation.

Fits perfectly as storage or as a pot cover for your plants.

Basket 16: ca H 20 cm x Ø 24 cm

HANDMADE IN KENYA

fields.name: Mud Cloth Pillow Cover - Bamako
fields.description:
This pillow is handmade with authentic hand dyed African Mud Cloth. The back of the pillow is natural colored linen with invisible zipper closure. 
Due to the handmade and vintage nature of these fabrics, it is recommended to spot clean and dry clean only.

About 19x19 square. 

PILLOW INSERT NOT INCLUDED.
